{"id":174167,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Street_furniture","text":"Street furniture is the equipment on streets and roads mostly for the safety of people and their information. The term is most used in the UK, Canada and Australia.\nIt includes benches, bollards, post boxes, phone boxes, street lighting, traffic lights, traffic signs, bus stops, grit bins, tram stops, taxi stands, public lavatories, fountains and memorials, and waste receptacles.\nAn important consideration in the design of street furniture is how it affects road safety.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"UK","surface_form":"UK","offset":139},{"uri":"Canada","surface_form":"Canada","offset":143},{"uri":"Australia","surface_form":"Australia","offset":154},{"uri":"Bench_(furniture)","surface_form":"benches","offset":177},{"uri":"Bollard","surface_form":"bollard","offset":186},{"uri":"Post_box","surface_form":"post box","offset":196},{"uri":"Phone_box","surface_form":"phone box","offset":208},{"uri":"Street_lighting","surface_form":"street lighting","offset":221},{"uri":"Traffic_light","surface_form":"traffic light","offset":238},{"uri":"Traffic_sign","surface_form":"traffic sign","offset":254},{"uri":"Bus_stop","surface_form":"bus stop","offset":269},{"uri":"Grit_bin","surface_form":"grit bin","offset":280},{"uri":"Tram_stop","surface_form":"tram stop","offset":291},{"uri":"Taxi_stand","surface_form":"taxi stand","offset":303},{"uri":"Fountain","surface_form":"fountain","offset":335},{"uri":"Memorial","surface_form":"memorial","offset":349},{"uri":"Waste_receptacles","surface_form":"waste receptacles","offset":364},{"uri":"Road_safety","surface_form":"road safety","offset":462}]}